  "texts": [
    "Prior works include efforts by Tu et al. (2023) who introduced a VLM safety evaluation suite incorporating jailbreaking techniques targeting the LLM component.",
    "Additionally, Qi et al. (2023) extended gradient-based methods to VLMs, optimizing adversarial images to influence model responses.",
    "Shayegani et al. (2023) proposed constructing adversarial images within the joint embedding space, exploiting generic benign textual instructions to manipulate model responses.",
    "Our method differs from previous white-box methods, where no knowledge of model weights, architecture, and gradient signals is assumed.",
    "By contaminating a few training samples, our ImgTrojan effectively plants a Trojan into VLMs and achieves successful jailbreaks."
